Product description

The Coleman 52 qt. Xtreme Cooler is perfect for weekend getaways, with the technology to keep ice up to five days in 90-degree weather and the capacity to hold 82 cans. It features two-way handles for easy lifting and carrying, and the rustproof, leak-resistant channel drain allows for no-tilt draining.   You know the name, and you?ll love the company. Coleman is unparalleled in the world of camping and outdoor gear. What started out as an innovation in gas-powered lamps over 100 years ago has grown to an international company that designs and constructs top-quality tents, lanterns, stoves, coolers, sleeping bags, and more. No matter what your outdoor sport: hiking, camping, fishing, hunting, boating, swimming, four-wheeling, relaxing, or tailgating, Coleman has what you need to help get you out there to enjoy it. Durable plastic construction. Features Xtreme 5 technology and Thermozone insulation. Designed to hold up to 82 cans. Includes hinged lid with 4 cup holders and 2-way handle. Dimensions: 27.75L x 14.95W x 17.25H in..

5.0 out of 5 starsAddressing those who wonder if this is appropriate for making a mash tun, or wondering what that even is....
ByMarkon March 30, 2017
Color: Blue|Verified Purchase
I purchased this to use as a mash tun for home brewing. Several users questioned whether the drain would work, etc. Let me assure you, I'm thrilled with it. The drain plug unscrews in standard fashion, leaving a bare standard 1/2" port to install your stainless ball valve. The construction is good with thick insulation in the the lid as well as the sides and bottom and there is good sloped drainage so you don't leave a lot of wort undrained at the end of your mash. I replaced the cheap plastic hinges with stainless steel ones I found on Amazon as well Coleman Stainless Steel Cooler Hinges and the stainless steel lid stay 11" Heavy Duty Stainless Steel Replacement Lid Strap for Igloo or Coleman Coolers although I suspect the chest would serve you well without these additions. Cheers
